headlines.description: Russell Wilson threw two touchdown passes and ran for another in his Wisconsin debut and Montee Ball scored four times to the 11th-ranked Badgers over UNLV 51-17 on Thursday night.

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Memphis Tigers

headlines.description: Vick Ballard rushed for 166 yards and three touchdowns and No. 20 Mississippi State easily handled Memphis 59-14 on Thursday night at the Liberty Bowl.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ballard leads Miss St. to opening win

events.name: Murray State Racers at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Will Stein threw for two touchdowns and 226 yards as Louisville beat Murray State 21-9 in the season opener for both teams on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisville kicks off season by beating Murray St.

events.name: South Carolina State Bulldogs at Central Michigan Chippewas
North Texas Mean Green at Florida Intl Golden Panthers
New Hampshire Wildcats at Toledo Rockets
West Alabama Tigers at South Alabama Jaguars
Western Carolina Catamounts at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Orwin Smith scored two of Georgia Tech's four first-quarter touchdowns, Stephen Hill caught two touchdown passes from Tevin Washington and Georgia Tech beat Western Carolina 63-21 on Thursday night in the opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia Tech scores 4 TDs in 1st, cruises to win

events.name: North Carolina Central Eagles at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Highly touted freshman Savon Huggins ran for two touchdowns and Rutgers started making amends for a disastrous 2010 season with a 48-0 victory over North Carolina Central on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Freshman Huggins runs for 2 TDs; Rutgers wins

events.name: UMass Minutemen at Holy Cross Crusaders
Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Van Chew made a diving 4-yard touchdown catch in the left flat at the goal line on the first series of overtime, and Syracuse rallied past Wake Forest 36-29 on Thursday night in the season-opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Syracuse rallies in 4th, stuns Wake Forest in OT

events.name: Montana State Bobcats at Utah Utes

headlines.description: John White rushed for 150 yards with two touchdowns in his major-college debut and Brian Blechen intercepted two passes as Utah opened with a 27-10 victory Thursday night over Montana State.
headlines.shortLinkText: White helps Utah win debut as Pac-12 member

events.name: Bowling Green Falcons at Idaho Vandals
Kentucky Wildcats at Western Kentucky Hilltoppers

headlines.description: Josh Clemons scored on a 14-yard touchdown run, and Morgan Newton shook off three interceptions in throwing a 31-yard TD pass to La'Rod King in helping the Wildcats beat Western Kentucky 14-3 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kentucky shakes slow start, holds off Hilltoppers

events.name: UC Davis Aggies at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.shortLinkText: Osweiler throws 2 TDs as Arizona State wins big
